cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its analyses, please cite it as below."
title: "jansky-research: A CPU-only, reproducible toolkit for amateur radio-astronomy analyses"
abstract: >-
  A tested, CPU-only Python toolkit for amateur, reproducible radio-astronomy
  analyses, built on the jansky course library. It bundles five public-data
  research slices — FRB burst statistics, FRB activity-periodicity, the Milky Way
  HI tangent-point rotation curve, a SETI Doppler-drift injection-recovery
  benchmark, and ultra-steep-spectrum source selection — each run on real public
  data, put through an adversarial science-review gate, and written up honestly
  (three validations and two negative/cautionary results).
type: software
